"The distribution is also called 'normal-inverse Gaussian distribution'..." This is a wrong description. Normal-inverse Gaussian (NIG) is different from inverse gaussian. NIG a mean-variance mixture of normal distribution and inverse Gaussion distribution.
See NIG at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Normal-inverse_Gaussian_distribution
See inverse gaussian at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Inverse_Gaussian_distribution
